<DOC><DOCNO> AP890807-0103 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-07-89 1853EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Israel-Army     08-07 0237</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Israel-Army,0244</SECOND><HEAD>Forty Percent of Future Recruits Surveyed Say They Hate Arabs</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A survey of 5,300 future Israeli army recruitsshowed that 40 percent ``hate most or all Arabs'' and 90 percentwould volunteer if they were not drafted, Israel army radio saidMonday.   It also indicated most high school students believe there willbe another Arab-Israeli war, the radio said, but did not give apercentage figures.   The survey, the first of its kind since the Palestinian uprisingagainst Israeli occupatio of West Bank and Gaza Strip began 20months ago, was conducted last year by a private research companyfor the Education Ministry.   It said 42 percent identified themselves as representing thepolitical right and 34 percent as leftists.   ``I think if we asked the general population the same questions,we would get similar answers,'' said Avraham Amir, director-generalof the Education Ministry.   He said the army and government try to educate soldiers not tohate Arabs, despite the continuing conflict.   Reuven Gel of the private Israel Institute for Military Studies,which conducted the survey, said researchers interviewed 5,300students aged 16 to 18 from high schools across the country.   Israeli men are drafted at 18 for a three-year tour of duty andcontinue doing reserve service of up to 45 days a year until age55. Women serve for two years and are not required to serve in thereserves.</TEXT></DOC>